## What Is This?

Without a linting step in the Jenkins pipeline, every Dockerfile anti-pattern from Phase 1 ships silently. Missing USER directives, ADD instead of COPY, unpinned base images, missing `--no-cache-dir` — none of these produce build errors. They just produce vulnerable images.

hadolint in Jenkins catches these at the earliest possible point — before the image is built, before it reaches ECR, before it runs in ECS. 30 seconds of CI time prevents the entire Phase 1 vulnerability class from reaching production.

